0 Ever wonder why Pacific Islanders seem to automatically assume the sense of humour of Black Americans ? regardless of their ethnic origins ? Well this film will not provide any answers to this often pondered question - but it will provide an excellent case study.<br /><br />From its onset this film acts as a sort of " Old School " for Pacific Island New Zealanders , which immediately raises the question what exactly is the point of such a task . Is it meant to perpetuate ingrained stereotypes of Pacific Island New Zealanders ? or is it intended to exploit this potential market ? The story is weak , jokes humorless , and the ending is expected . This film has done nothing for New Zealand cinema , as it is merely an appropriated romantic comedy that is devoid of any merit .
