0 Anyone who 's watched a few Lifetime Movie Network movies knows that plot credibility is the first thing that gets brushed off the planning table . So , when crazed Lara moves into Patti 's home and methodically begins to drive her landlady bonkers , I did n't even blink . When Lara eventually ramps up her activities to threatening poor Patti , and dares her to do anything about it , I just nodded . You see , on Planet LMN , people do n't behave the way they do for any particular reason , they just do it to keep the action going . Only on Planet LMN could someone almost have the owner of a home thrown out of their own house by means of their seductive powers ! ! Poor Patti - she just trusted too much , and Lara went off her medicine , and then there was this big fight at the top of the stairs involving a syringe full of deadly stuff that ends up injected into someone 's tummy , and a body bag going out the front door . The horror!<br /><br />But take it from me , this Planet LMN product is a classic . You need to watch it once , just for the great laughs you 'll have . On the Improbability Scale , I give this film a 95/100 . Make a big batch of popcorn and get some apple slices , too . You 'll understand later .
